I will be drawing webtoons probably. I do not have personal memory since 2016, which means this will continue until 2019

00:29:41.000 --> 00:29:45.000
I will be drawing. I hope I will survive

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:50.000
Yes. I wish to keep subscribe your webtoons

00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:55.000
Please make sure to buy me virtual coins

00:29:57.000 --> 00:30:13.000
Now I will toss it to the audience for Q&amp;A session. Please raise your hand if you would like to ask anything to her

00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:21.000
Please feel free to ask personal questions such as what game do you play? Oh I play Candy Crush by the way

00:30:26.000 --> 00:30:29.000
Hi I am an engineer at Google

00:30:29.000 --> 00:30:41.000
You shared challenges in webtoon industry and, as a matter of fact, software industry went through the same

00:30:41.000 --> 00:30:51.000
Copying software program became a normal practice and people were fooled for using software out of their pocket

00:30:51.000 --> 00:31:00.000
Anyway, I think there are ways to make improvements along the way

00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:12.000
What kind of changes do you think it will make positive impacts in your industry?

00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:25.000
The portal where I post World History Talk was established by a publishing company

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:42.000
I was convinced when I heard of Wisdom House launched webtoon business because they have a long history of exchanging scripts with authors

00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:59.000
In other words, we went through a dark age where authors were arrested due to censorship, and there were editor who visited imprisoned authors in person with snacks to check on their status

00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:18.000
They show courtesy to the authors. So you know you are respected as you talk to them, even though they are rookie

00:32:18.000 --> 00:32:31.000
They might experience trial and error in the beginning, but I was convinced that they will be directed towards the right path

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:40.000
As a matter of fact, authors are often offended because they are in close communication with the readers

00:32:40.000 --> 00:32:48.000
Wisdom House take actions to protect the authors or send presents during Korean Thanksgiving

00:32:48.000 --> 00:32:53.000
Most of all, they giveaway free books since they are publisher

00:32:53.000 --> 00:33:11.000
They feed the authors both physically and intellectually and show respect to authors that they deserve

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:17.000
In return, I did my best on my end as well. I didn't feel like being a printer

00:33:17.000 --> 00:33:20.000
I am explicitly promoting Justoon

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:31.000
Please subscribe and also monitor them as well because I have witness many publishers that launched a new business with healthy motive, but soon became materialized

00:33:31.000 --> 00:33:44.000
They forgot the core business value, which resulted in losing both trust and readers

00:33:44.000 --> 00:33:56.000
Webtoon market has a short history with 15 years. However, the rise and fall has been very dynamic and there a lot to learn from it

00:33:56.000 --> 00:34:10.000
What I learned is to show professional respect to those I work with that they deserve

00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:23.000
This is very fundamental thing to do, yet it is difficult to be consistent. I think even a word era is outdated given the pace of changes we face

00:34:23.000 --> 00:34:27.000
A challenge is replaced by another and we will face new challenges overnight

00:34:27.000 --> 00:34:37.000
New challenges come with new roles, however, what does not change tasks managed by human

00:34:37.000 --> 00:34:54.000
Human is the most important. I recall only three people in my industry who stick to that principle

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:20.000
I have two questions. One is the web ecosystem

00:35:20.000 --> 00:35:30.000
It seems that the industry keeps growing, although wealth distribution is another matter

00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:46.000
There are new players in the market that plans and creates contents as a middle person like YLAB.

00:35:46.000 --> 00:35:51.000
Could you please explain how you cooperate with YLAB?

00:35:51.000 --> 00:36:10.000
Also, you seem to do research on tones and languages, but I find that tones from your characters differ from one another

00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:30.000
Especially Cao Cao and Yuan Shao from The Three Kingdom have unique tone. Do you have any research object for benchmark?

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:35.000
It is an interesting question

00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:46.000
My relationship with YLAB? I am good with them

00:36:46.000 --> 00:37:00.000
Our relationship is combination of fandom, loyalty, family and they also help me with money and legal issues

00:37:00.000 --> 00:37:18.000
When I say something and it is contractual issue, they would review even though it is against their profit

00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:29.000
If copyright or malicious comment issues occur during the review, they would hire a lawyer for me

00:37:29.000 --> 00:37:42.000
Because you will see tons of weirdoes from historical webtoons. The genuine history maniacs would be on my side, but those who pretend to be offend me

00:37:50.000 --> 00:38:04.000
In addition, there are authors at YLAB and they are my colleague, subscriber, and fan and working with them definitely synergize

00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:35.000
It is a desirable business model, but investors will get involved to expand their business later on. I hope they move towards a right direction

00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:42.000
Moving on to the next question, I think tone represents your identity

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:46.000
You will notice that people use different tone at group chats

00:38:46.000 --> 00:39:01.000
Elders tend to finish the sentence with multiple dots and shorten their sentence as if they can never write more than three lines and etc

00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:17.000
I did not pay much attention to it in the beginning, but it turns out that their life is immersed into their tones

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:47.000
Non-verbal expression is critical as well and each one has its model, including a number of King from Joseon and characters from The Three Kingdom

00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:55.000
In The Three Kingdom, Yuan Shao is full of non-verbal expressions. He does not initiate any conversation

00:40:13.000 --> 00:40:39.000
Most of people believe that the Three Kingdom is represented by Liu Bei, Cao Cao, and the Son family, but I would say 70% of the story deals with different characters

00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:52.000
Yuan Shao is from a noble family and he does not initiate conversation

00:40:52.000 --> 00:40:58.000
If he has to, he would only start a chat with Cao Cao by just calling his name

00:40:52.000 --> 00:41:07.000
In reality, people with high profile would call my name first and remain silent until I answer back

00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:15.000
They will call my name multiple time until I finally answer back

00:41:15.000 --> 00:41:24.000
For example, if my script needs to be edited, editors usually just ask me to do so

00:41:24.000 --> 00:41:29.000
However, high rank officers first summon me before digging into main agenda

00:41:29.000 --> 00:41:31.000
Yuan Shao would always call Cao Cao name first before initiating the main conversation

00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:37.000
Aman is Cao Cao nick name and he would call Aman repeatedly until he answers

00:41:37.000 --> 00:42:02.000
Cao Cao spent the most of his early years with loyalty. He killed those violated the boundary of law, and did not commit habitual killing

00:42:02.000 --> 00:42:13.000
He got sick of the law system at his time and sought for power

00:42:14.000 --> 00:42:20.000
He was very busy as to lose his humanity, which is immersed in the way he communicate

00:42:20.000 --> 00:42:33.000
Cao Cao does not go more than a sentence when he talks to his family and complete his sentence with noun followed by period

00:42:33.000 --> 00:42:42.000
My friends studying law are obsessed with putting period to finish sentences

00:43:10.000 --> 00:43:13.000
Last question?

00:43:14.000 --> 00:43:19.000
I will take two more. The one in red and blue

00:43:21.000 --> 00:43:30.000
You mentioned that you upload six episodes per week for three series

00:43:31.000 --> 00:43:40.000
You are so busy that you cannot even really remember the last movie you watched. You are committed to you works without personal life

00:43:40.000 --> 00:44:00.000
How long does it take for you to draw one episode and which aspect of your work is the most time consuming? Do you have assistants? If so, what is their role?

00:44:01.000 --> 00:44:10.000
The majority of my time goes to The Three Kingdoms Talk

00:44:10.000 --> 00:44:20.000
I usually spend five days on it and split the other two days on The World History and Joseon Wangjo Sil Talk

00:44:20.000 --> 00:44:31.000
I am pretty used to Joseon Wangjo Sil Talk at this stage and it does not take more than a day

00:44:31.000 --> 00:44:42.000
I have more know-hows to come up with new episode themes. For example, what is the day today by the way?

00:44:43.000 --> 00:44:50.000
Battle of Myeongnyang took place today. Today is Oct 28th right?

00:44:50.000 --> 00:44:53.000
25th

00:44:53.000 --> 00:45:08.000
Look at me..For example, I used to have the dates of historical events on my cell phone calendar, including the birthday of kings of Joseon, anniversary or the date of death and etc

00:45:08.000 --> 00:45:13.000
Joseon Wangjo Sil Talk is updated on every Wednesday and Sunday so it is easier for me choose theme and put them into day-based frame

00:45:13.000 --> 00:45:34.000
Also, I have been doing a special episode on Hangul Day for five consecutive years along with Korean New Year and Thanksgiving Day to talk about Korean traditional rites

00:45:34.000 --> 00:45:45.000
I also try to address social issues at the time of writing such as college tuition and housing prices etc., which apparently had to be dealt with centuries ago

00:45:34.000 --> 00:45:50.000
For example, public officers in Joseon had to let go 90% of their salary for housing to work in Seoul

00:45:50.000 --> 00:45:55.000
I do not much struggle to come up with new episode ideas for Joseon Wangjo Sil Talk

00:45:55.000 --> 00:45:59.000
Once I know what to write about, then rest of the process does not take that long

00:46:00.000 --> 00:46:12.000
The Three Kingdom Talk takes much longer because it is not easy for me to decide which scenes that the subscribers are interested to read

00:46:12.000 --> 00:46:18.000
The Three Kingdom is very interesting by itself

00:46:18.000 --> 00:46:30.000
The real historical events took place almost 2,000 years ago then the story was novelized nearly 600 years ago and it has been passed down since then

00:46:30.000 --> 00:46:37.000
However, The Three Kingdom seem to be very old-fashioned at its first glance as if only those in 50s would read

00:46:37.000 --> 00:46:59.000
So I think of ways to make it more accessible to young readers who can sympathize

00:46:59.000 --> 00:47:09.000
I changed Chinese ranks into terms that Koreans are more familiar with

00:47:09.000 --> 00:47:21.000
For 1 on 1 battle, I replaced it with screen capture or youtube format

00:47:21.000 --> 00:47:31.000
For the scene where you make order to the adviser, I used the setting where the adviser is invited to a group chat to receive the order

00:47:31.000 --> 00:47:39.000
This is my first level of transformation

00:47:39.000 --> 00:47:43.000
The second level of transformation is change in emphasis

00:47:43.000 --> 00:47:53.000
To sympathize with the new generation, it should no longer be Liu Fei and Cao Cao that we all know

00:47:53.000 --> 00:48:14.000
Martial arts was the key to success 20 years ago. Million copies were guaranteed

00:48:14.000 --> 00:48:28.000
However, the same paradigm will not sustain a month in these days because our generation grew up watching the monitor

00:48:28.000 --> 00:48:35.000
They do not get used to wide screen or even detailed pictures

00:48:35.000 --> 00:48:44.000
As the key viewing channel is shifting from PC to mobile, authors started to spend less time in drawing cuts because even well-made pictures are distorted to certain extent in mobile format

00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:49.000
People no longer reads so the length of lines shortened

00:48:49.000 --> 00:49:04.000
The Three Kingdom is a soap opera with scale so my main struggle was changing the point of view to the first person perspective

00:49:04.000 --> 00:49:30.000
For example, the webtoon begins with Liu Fei who is 23 year-old employed where he ask google whether 23 year-old jobless living in mom's house should kill himself or not

00:49:30.000 --> 00:49:41.000
Cao Cao who was a public officer would say something like this damn country should fail as an attempt to change the world

00:49:41.000 --> 00:49:49.000
Or I turned Yuan Shao who likes getting attention into a social media celebrity

00:49:49.000 --> 00:50:07.000
Describing their desire and ambition in 21st century language is challenging because I do not meet many people to have desires

00:50:07.000 --> 00:50:24.000
I just want to sleep. This is my concern. I know I am committed to my work, but I feel isolated from the society

00:50:24.000 --> 00:50:32.000
I wonder whether my work brings value. Does 24 hour that I spend help hungry kids in Kenya?

00:50:32.000 --> 00:50:36.000
I feel this disparity when I travel

00:50:36.000 --> 00:50:47.000
I think building a house for Habitat brings much more value than drawing webtoons, but I have not traveled in recent 5 years

00:50:47.000 --> 00:50:54.000
Being honest with my desire is good..not forgetting that I am a human being

00:50:54.000 --> 00:51:10.000
Then I think I will be able to find various themes. I have to be humane first to understand how others think

00:51:12.000 --> 00:51:14.000
The one in blue

00:51:17.000 --> 00:51:22.000
Hi. I am an engineer at Google

00:51:26.000 --> 00:51:32.000
Your story was interesting and the way your put them together was fun as well

00:51:32.000 --> 00:51:42.000
I thought you could give me advice. How can I become a fun story teller? 

00:51:42.000 --> 00:52:00.000
You also talked about AI. In AI era, you mentioned that people will seek entertainment over productivity. What categorize entertainment in AI era?

00:52:00.000 --> 00:52:12.000
I do not think fun stories are out of creativity. It comes from observation. It is a long process

00:52:12.000 --> 00:52:16.000
I have a good educational background just like everyone in this room

00:52:16.000 --> 00:52:26.000
It means that you theoretically understand fun. In other words, you cannot do something that makes you look undermined

00:52:26.000 --> 00:52:39.000
I made a big hit with Joseon Wangjo Sil Talk as a webtoonist. But I thought myself as a noble, studious and cynical person

00:52:39.000 --> 00:52:49.000
I would pursue the truth to become light to this world and looked deep inside, thinking that I would every possible desire in me

00:52:49.000 --> 00:53:00.000
I was seen as an author with many subscribers, but our interest is making money to be honest

00:53:00.000 --> 00:53:04.000
Money is good

00:53:04.000 --> 00:53:12.000
There are things that I want to enjoy by paying money and that is good for me

00:53:12.000 --> 00:53:18.000
Maybe I like too much coins but anyways I want to make money and be successful

00:53:18.000 --> 00:53:21.000
That is how I get paid for my salary・to protect the server

00:53:21.000 --> 00:53:33.000
I need to observe others in more detail to be paid even more. Contemporary people are very unique

00:53:33.000 --> 00:53:41.000
Consumer, reader, Netizen are all same group of people, but the way they communicate is very unique

00:53:41.000 --> 00:53:51.000
You have to witness with your own eyes. There are several differences that I feel as an author

00:53:51.000 --> 00:54:00.000
First, the way of thinking has been changed. They do not get metaphor anymore

00:54:00.000 --> 00:54:12.000
In the past, people knew what it meant to be delightful with tears in their eye or being cold to someone when you actually love them inside

00:54:12.000 --> 00:54:22.000
This does not work anymore. When someone is angry, they will only believe it when I emphasize that they are angry

00:54:22.000 --> 00:54:32.000
They will have to accept it. People do not want me to use rhetoric for explanation

00:54:32.000 --> 00:54:45.000
This is very interesting. But we are busy, especially inside of the building

00:54:45.000 --> 00:55:06.000
I am captivated inside of well decorated building for my word, but you need to use time to meet people for observation

00:55:06.000 --> 00:55:10.000
At the same time meeting people is tiring

00:55:10.000 --> 00:55:21.000
I get uncomfortable when I encounter someone having different thoughts, especially when they are younger

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:31.000
I have that resistance in me. Maybe it is because I am stubborn or level of my education

00:55:31.000 --> 00:55:42.000
However, I have to invest my time and be patient with them and observe until I understand

00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:48.000
When I do not understand their pattern, I need to memorize them at least. This is painful

00:55:48.000 --> 00:55:59.000
I used to enjoy using elegant words, but my subscribers are 4th graders

00:55:59.000 --> 00:56:10.000
I have to put everything in the view of 4th graders. I actually learned this from one producer

00:56:11.000 --> 00:56:23.000
One day, I talked to a producer with milestone programs. Their world is very intense and competitive. You never know when to get fired

00:56:23.000 --> 00:56:32.000
Then I asked him for know-how and he said that if you can make a program that 8th grader understands, then the rest of humanity would understand

00:56:32.000 --> 00:56:41.000
That happened four years ago and that was very helpful advice. 

00:56:41.000 --> 00:56:54.000
I only imagined subscribers ranging from 20 to 30 year old. I targeted 8th graders as my potential reader and he said that it has been pushed down to 4th grader. Humanity evolves

00:56:57.000 --> 00:57:04.000
You should remember this 4th grader rule. This is not something to laugh about

00:57:04.000 --> 00:57:18.000
Everyone in this room should be 4th grader. Do you know how hard it is? Because it comes with a sense of shame

00:57:18.000 --> 00:57:23.000
Why did I go to college and paid tuition if I have to put myself into 4th grader's position?

00:57:23.000 --> 00:57:34.000
My colleagues say that they wish they are 11th graders. Then they can write milestone episodes

00:57:47.000 --> 00:57:50.000
Does it answer your question?

00:57:53.000 --> 00:58:04.000
There is an impressive quote from your other interview. You said that you draw historical cartoons, but its essence is ordinary life and human story

00:58:04.000 --> 00:58:15.000
I hope you would continue to keep this sharp sense of observation to provide us with great contents

